    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that they're different frameworks, but in a real debate, how do you actually judge which one is \"better\"? like, if you had to pick a primary ethical principle to base a society on, wouldn't the universal rights of a person (asylum) naturally outweigh the political concept of a border? it feels like one is based on human life and the other is just about lines on a map.",
